name: CryptoMushrooms #005 - Mycena Pura
description:
This is one of the most beautiful species of Mycena, also know as “Lilac Bonnet”. It contains a small amount of the poison muscarine and should not be eaten. Like many other species in the genus Mycena, the Lilac Bonnet is reported to be bioluminescent, emitting a weak green light (wavelength in the region of of 520 to 530 nanometres). This is a common species in both deciduous and coniferous woodland, but it also occurs in some grassland sites.
